text: thumb The Cathedral of Our Lady of Mount Carmel (Katedral Santa Maria Bunda Karmel) is a Roman Catholic cathedral in Malang, East Java, Indonesia, and seat of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Malang. The cathedral was built in 1934 in the neo-gothic style by architect L. Estourgie, and is an example of the Dutch colonial architectural heritage in the city. It was originally named for St Teresa but was renamed in 1961. ==References== Category:Religious buildings and structures in East Java Category:Roman Catholic cathedrals in Indonesia Category:Roman Catholic churches completed in 1934 Category:Churches in Java Category:1934 establishments in the Dutch East Indies
